  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/Ekhtear-Ahmed-Zeesan.jpg?itok=0sGxUeD8",
  "bio_raw": "Ekhtear Ahmed Zeesan started his career in June 2022 as a Management Trainee Officer at Industrial and Infrastructure Development Finance Company (IIDFC) Limited. He worked there for around 6 months with the Structured Finance team. Having immense passion for teaching, he shifted himself from the industry in December 2022. As an academician, he commenced his career at EXIM Bank Agricultural University Bangladesh and stayed there for a trimester. After that, he joined the FBA of Eastern University and taught there for around 10 months.\nRight now he is doing great as a Lecturer at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB). Apart from teaching, Zeesan is actively involved with research-based activities. He is also working as a consultant for the Institutional Quality Assurance Cell of ULAB. Additionally, he is working as the advisor of Hult Prize at ULAB, one of the most prestigious sustainable entrepreneurship events supported by ULAB School of Business.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Public Policy, Financial Technology, Sustainable Finance, Carbon Finance, Behavioral Finance, Digital Currencies, Capital Market, Regulatory Compliance."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMBA\nin Finance and Banking, 2022\nBangladesh University of Professionals\nBBA\nin Finance and Banking, 2021\nBangladesh University of Professionals"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nZeesan, E. A.\n, Uddin, M. K., Tarique, K. M., Ahmed, S. U., Ahmed, M. U., & Siddiqui, S. H. (2025). Navigating Interest Rate Flux: Evidence from South and Southeast Asia.\nInternational Journal of Accounting and Economics Studies, 12 (2), 232-241\n.\nhttps://doi.org/10.14419/\nhmcxbd30\nRafi, M.M.A,\nZeesan, E.A.\n, Natasha, M.T., Mahruf, R., & Ahmed, F. (2020). Financial Performance Analysis of Some Selected Investment Banks of Bangladesh.\nJournal of Internet Banking and Commerce, 25 (3)\n.\nIslam, N.,\nZeesan, E.A.\n, Chakraborty, D., Rahman, M.N., Ahmed, S.I.U., Nower, N., & Nazrul, T. (2019). Relationship between Job Stress and the Turnover Intention of Private Sector Bank Employees in Bangladesh.\nInternational Business Research, 12 (8)\n.\nhttps://doi.org/10.5539/ibr.\nv12n8p133",
